<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            Embassy in France</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v03</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d81</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">81</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-03-01T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-03-01T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/3–149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-01T18:00:00-05:00">March 1, 1949—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>639. Personal for the Amb. Believe it might be useful if you make informal
                    suggestion to <persName corresp="#p_SR1">Schuman</persName> that <persName corresp="#p_K1">Koenig</persName> be instructed facilitate agreement on
                    basic law text.<note n="1" xml:id="d81fn1">In telegram 168, February 28, from
                        Frankfurt, not printed, <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName> had
                        proposed that it might be useful for <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Caffery</persName> to suggest to <persName corresp="#p_SR1">Schuman</persName> that <persName corresp="#p_K1">Koenig</persName> be
                        instructed to facilitate the approval of the Basic Law.
                        (862.044/2–2849)</note> Polit advisers near agreement on report to Mil Govs
                    re Bonn draft (Frankfurt tel 19 to Paris<note n="2" xml:id="d81fn2">Same as
                        telegram 144, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note>) and Dept hopes approval will not be unduly delayed in view
                    embarrassment to Bonn assembly, generally unfavorable polit effect in Germany,
                    and adverse effect on trizonal program.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
